1. L-VALUE ERROR — Cannot assign to non-variable (expression)

@int x is 2$
5 is x$


2. BASIC DECLARATIONS — int, float, char, const
@int x$
@float y is 3.14$
@char c is 'a'$
fixed @int z is 10$


3. EXPRESSIONS — arithmetic, type promotion

@int a is 10$
@float b is 20.5$
@int c is a + 5$
@float d is b * 2.0$
@int result is a + b$


4. CONTROL FLOW — if, while loop

@int x is 10$
when (x gt 5) begin  
    @int y is 20$
end
loop (x lt 100) begin
    x is x + 1$
end


5. SCOPES — inner scope can access outer variables

@int global is 100$
begin
    @int local1 is 10$
    begin
        @int local2 is 20$
        @int sum is global + local1 + local2$
    end
end


6. FUNCTIONS — declaration and call

func @int add(@int a, @int b) begin
    ret a + b$
end

func @void display() begin
    @int x is 42$
end

@int result = call add(3, 4)$


